    "fullBio": [
      "Oreoluwa Olusoga is an intelligent, resourceful, and results-driven professional accountant with strong analytical and leadership capabilities. She possesses extensive experience in financial reporting, audit management, regulatory compliance, and advisory services. As an Assistant Manager, Audit & Assurance Services at TAC Professional Services, she plays a key role in driving the firm's commitment to excellence and client-focused service delivery.",
      "Oreoluwa began her career at Eko Electricity Distribution Company as an Accountant, before joining TAC Professional Services in 2024. Through dedication, technical competence, and strong leadership, she rose through the ranks to her current position, where she oversees complex audit and advisory engagements across multiple sectors.",
      "She has successfully led teams in delivering high-impact Audit & Assurance, Forensic Investigation, Due Diligence, and IFRS Advisory assignments. Her professional experience spans critical sectors of the economy, including Oil & Gas, Telecommunications, Financial Services, and Manufacturing, where she has consistently delivered exceptional results marked by precision, compliance, and strategic insight.",
      "Oreoluwa holds a Bachelor's Degree in Accounting from the University of Lagos (2018) and is an Associate Member of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria (ICAN). She actively participates in ICAN MCPE programs and Integra International workshops, continuously enhancing her technical expertise and consulting acumen."
